---
import "../global.css";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import miika from "./miika.jpg";
---

<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Miika Leinonen - Home</title>
  </head>
  <body class="font-mono bg-gray-50 w-full">
    <main>
      <!-- Hero Section -->
      <section
        class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-16"
      >
        <div>
          <h1 class="font-sans text-3xl">Miika Leinonen</h1>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <a href="https://github.com/miikalei">
              <img src="/src/pages/github.svg" width="30" /></a
            >
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/miikaleinonen/">
              <img src="/src/pages/linkedin.svg" width="30" />
            </a>
            <a href="/">
              <img src="/src/pages/world.svg" width="30" />
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <Image
          style={{
            clipPath: "circle()",
          }}
          src={miika}
          alt="Image of a handsome young pro, battle bruised but still full of young energy"
          width={200}
        />
      </section>

      <!-- Introduction -->
      <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
        <p class="text-lg">
          Hello, My name is Miika. I am a professional software engineer, based
          in Helsinki, Finland. I am serious about honing my craft, and I take
          pride in my producing code that is as stable, performant and secure as
          possible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Projects Section -->
      <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Stuff I have built</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Upright</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              <a href="https://www.uprightproject.com/">Upright</a> is a company
              that develops a macroeconomic model in order to gain a holistic view
              on impact footprints of products, companies and funds. I joined this
              adventure in the year 2021, and have been mainly focusing on the internal
              and external web app functionality to handle the large amounts of data
              produced. Visit the <a href="https://uprightplatform.com/"
                >Upright platform</a
              > to see the results!
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">MLox interpreter</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              To follow the excellent book <a
                href="https://craftinginterpreters.com/"
                >Crafting interpreters</a
              > by Robert Nystrom, I implemented my own mod of the interpreted language
              built in the book. The (toy) language is called mlox, and you can try
              it in the browser
              <a href="/mlox">here</a>. The interpreter is written in
              Typescript, and its source is available <a
                href="https://github.com/miikalei/mlox">here.</a
              >
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">This website</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              The website you are viewing right now is built with Astro and
              served with GitHub pages. It utilizes React components and
              Tailwind. Check out the source on <a
                href="https://github.com/miikalei/miikalei.github.io">GitHub</a
              >.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Miscellaneous exercises</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              <p>
                I like solving simple structured programming puzzles for the
                easy comparisons to alternative solutions. Check out my <a
                  href="https://github.com/miikalei/aoc"
                  >Advent of Code solutions (in Rust)</a
                > and <a href="https://github.com/miikalei/project-euler"
                  >Project Euler solutions (in Python)</a
                >. I also play CTFs at <a href="https://overthewire.org"
                  >Overthewire.org</a
                >.
              </p>
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Education -->
      <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Education</h2>
        <p>
          Master of Science and Bachelod of Science at Aalto University, 300
          ETCS, 2015-2021. Graduated with honors, with GPA 4.95 / 5.
        </p>
        <p>
          Main focus of my studies was on pure mathematics, with minority focus
          on computer science, graphics and ML.
        </p>
        <p>
          My master's thesis, <a
            href="https://aaltodoc.aalto.fi/items/16c62b40-2245-4875-a6e8-33661bed8393"
            >Federated Multi-task Learning over Networked Data</a
          >, is freely available for reading. My bachelor's thesis, <a
            href="https://aaltodoc.aalto.fi/items/5422ef14-df68-415b-bb6a-ab8d008c7849"
            >Quaternion algebras and well-rounded lattices</a
          >, is available only in the Aalto University library.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Technologies -->
      <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Technologies I've used</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Languages</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li>
                <strong>Typescript</strong> – Most professsional experience, frontend,
                backend and scripting
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Python</strong> – Mainly for data analysis and scripting
              </li>
              <li><strong>C/C++</strong> – Graphics and big math</li>
              <li><strong>Rust</strong> – Hobbyist, exercises</li>
              <li><strong>Scala</strong> – University courses only</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Backend & DevOps</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li><strong>PostgreSQL</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Node</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Docker</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Docker swarm</strong></li>
              <li><strong>AWS</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Linux</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Opentelemetry</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Jaeger</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Prometheus</strong></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Frontend</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li>React</li>
              <li>HTML/CSS</li>
              <li>Astro</li>
              <li>Tailwind</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Data analysis</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li>Python notebooks</li>
              <li>Scipy</li>
              <li>Pytorch</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer
    class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 w-full py-8 flex flex-col justify-center items-center"
  >
    <p>Miika Leinonen, 2025</p>
    <p>
      Check out the website <a
        href="https://github.com/miikalei/miikalei.github.io">source</a
      >
    </p>
  </footer>
</html>
